    },
    {
      "text": "A case-control study is being conducted by researchers to investigate the association between the onset of cardiovascular disease (CVD) and a high-calorie diet. Which of the following scenarios best reflects a form of Neyman bias?",
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "A",
          "text": "Asking participants to recall and report their dietary habits over the past five years.",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "B",
          "text": "Excluding cases who had CVD in the past but have since died or fully recovered.",
          "correct": true
        },
        {
          "label": "C",
          "text": "Including cases as patients admitted with CVD and controls as patients admitted for non-CVD causes",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "D",
          "text": "Publishing findings with a strong association, while those with inconclusive associations are unpublished.",
          "correct": false
        }
      ],
      "correct_answer": "B. Excluding cases who had CVD in the past but have since died or fully recovered.",
      "question_images": [],
      "explanation_images": [],
      "explanation": "<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:624px\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Neyman bias</strong><br/>\n<strong>(Option B)</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Known as prevalence-incidence bias occurs when a study excludes individuals who have died or recovered from the disease.</li>\n<li>Missing cases lead to an underestimation of the true association.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Berksonian bias</strong></p>\n<p><strong>(Option C)</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>A <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"88261f221b169277719869abab319a\">selection bias</span> by choosing hospitalised patients with multiple comorbidities as the study population</li>\n<li>Leads to a distorted association between exposure and outcome.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Reporting bias</strong><br/>\n<strong>(Option A)</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Information reporting is influenced by the knowledge of the desired outcome or the interest of the researchers.</li>\n<li>E.g., CVD patients may attribute their condition to past dietary habits leading to high-fat consumption, while those without CVD may underreport unhealthy eating habits.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Publication bias</strong></p>\n<p><strong>(Option D)</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Studies with positive or significant results are more likely to be published than studies with negative or non-significant results.</li>\n<li>This leads to an overrepresentation of studies showing a strong association between high-fat diets and CVD, potentially misleading readers.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n\n\n<p style='font-size: 10px; color: #808080; font-style: italic;'></p>",
      "bot": "@dams_new_robot",
      "audio": "https://image.prepladder.com/content/HPClEmAruNS5v76uI9kN1745949826.mp3",
