    {
      "text": "Which of the following statements best describes the purpose of double blinding in clinical trials",
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "A",
          "text": "It fails to avoid performance bias",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "B",
          "text": "It avoids both subject and observer bias",
          "correct": true
        },
        {
          "label": "C",
          "text": "Patients and the control group are unaware of their enrollment in a research trial.",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "D",
          "text": "It avoids selection bias",
          "correct": false
        }
      ],
      "correct_answer": "B. It avoids both subject and observer bias",
      "question_images": [],
      "explanation_images": [],
      "explanation": "<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:624px\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Blinding levels in Clinical trials</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>1. Single-blinded blinding</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Participants are unaware of the intervention</li>\n<li>Prevent biases that arise from knowledge of the treatment.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>2. Double-blinded blinding</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Both the researchers and participants are unaware of the intervention given <strong>(prevents observer and subject bias)</strong> <strong>(</strong><strong>Option </strong><strong> B and C)</strong></li>\n<li>Most <strong>common</strong> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a1b06f401f1692777203a53393ba98\">form</span> of blinding</li>\n<li>Avoids <strong>performance bias</strong> (associated with knowledge of treatment) <strong>(</strong><strong>Option </strong><strong> A)</strong></li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>3. Triple-blinded blinding</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Researchers, participants, and analysers are unaware of the intervention.</li>\n<li>The <strong>best</strong> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a1b06f401f1692777203a53393ba98\">form</span> of blinding.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n\n\n<p style='font-size: 10px; color: #808080; font-style: italic;'></p>",
      "bot": "@dams_new_robot",
      "audio": "https://image.prepladder.com/content/fhSqDF9o5RCjHzfwWYT81746271518.mp3",
