    },
    {
      "text": "Researchers found a significant correlation in a study examining the association between coffee drinking and heart disease. However, further analysis revealed that smoking might be influencing this relationship. In this context, smoking is considered as",
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "A",
          "text": "Causal variable",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "B",
          "text": "Random error",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "C",
          "text": "Confounding factor",
          "correct": true
        },
        {
          "label": "D",
          "text": "Spurious correlation",
          "correct": false
        }
      ],
      "correct_answer": "C. Confounding factor",
      "question_images": [],
      "explanation_images": [],
      "explanation": "<p style='font-size: 10px; color: #808080; font-style: italic;'></p>",
      "bot": "@dams_new_robot",
      "audio": "https://image.prepladder.com/content/60EBPVxwZRsMNp7YnnL91746271631.mp3",
      "video": "",
      "uid": "1e3f29c4"
    },
    {
      "text": "Q. Match the following: 1. Randomisation a. Eliminates only the known confounders. 2. Standardisation b. Eliminate the effect of age and gender. 3. Restriction c. Eliminates both known and unknown confounders. 4. Matching d. Limits the participation in the study to individuals who are similar concerning confounders.",
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "A",
          "text": "1-a, 2-b, 3-c, 4-d",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "B",
          "text": "1-b, 2-a, 3-d, 4-c",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "C",
          "text": "1-c, 2-b, 3-d, 4-a",
          "correct": true
        },
        {
          "label": "D",
          "text": "1-d, 2-c, 3-a, 4-b",
          "correct": false
        }
      ],
      "correct_answer": "C. 1-c, 2-b, 3-d, 4-a",
      "question_images": [],
      "explanation_images": [],
      "explanation": "<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:741px\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"3\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Techniques To Eliminate Confounders</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Method</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Description</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Examples</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Matching</strong></p>\n<br/>\n\t\t\t\u00a0</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Cases are matched with the control and should be similar to the control in every possible variable that can affect the study's outcome except the disease in question.</li>\n<li>Done in a case-control study.</li>\n<li><strong>Eliminates only the known confounders.</strong></li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>In a study on the effect of a new teaching method, students are matched based on their prior academic performance and then assigned to different groups.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Restriction</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Limits participation in the study to individuals who are similar in terms of confounders.</strong></li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>In a study, Restricting the study to only non-smokers will eliminate the effect of smoking.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Randomisation</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>The technique where every participant will get an equal and known chance of being allocated to either the treatment group or the control group.</li>\n<li><strong>Eliminates both known and unknown confounders.</strong></li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>In a clinical trial, patients are randomly assigned to receive either a new drug or a placebo, balancing out <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"fe39bb8df416927771849b06e48169\">confounding</span> variables.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Stratification (Segregate)</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Stratify the participants of the study or segregate them.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>In a clinical trial, to eliminate the effect of smoking as a confounder, one can further stratify or segregate participants into smokers and non-smokers.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Standardisation</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Adjusting the results to a standard population to control for <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"fe39bb8df416927771849b06e48169\">confounding</span> variables often used in rate comparisons</li>\n<li><strong>Eliminate or control the effect of age and gender.</strong></li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>In a study comparing mortality rates between two countries, rates are standardised to a common age distribution to control for age differences.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Multivariate <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"f30740eaeb16927771978fc4c375eb\">regression</span> models</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Used when there are multiple confounders.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>In an observational diet and heart disease study, a <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"f30740eaeb16927771978fc4c375eb\">regression</span> model is used to adjust for age, gender, and physical activity.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n\n\n<p style='font-size: 10px; color: #808080; font-style: italic;'></p>",
      "bot": "@dams_new_robot",
