      "explanation": "<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:659px\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Type of Association</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Description</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>1. <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"8700db0ae4169277719988f170583c\">Spurious</span> (Option A)</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>An association that appears to be present but is actually due to chance or an error in data.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Ice cream sales and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5031a7245c1692777186f7e7aabc06\">drowning</span> incidents</strong>:\n\n\t\t\t\t<ul>\n<li>Higher ice cream sales are associated with more <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5031a7245c1692777186f7e7aabc06\">drowning</span> incidents, but this is spurious. The real factor is summer, which increases both swimming activity and ice cream sales.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>2. <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"2f73e160ba1692777190d65065c95b\">Indirect</span> (Option B)</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>An association in which a third variable (known as the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"fe39bb8df416927771849b06e48169\">confounding</span> variable) causes both the predictor and the outcome.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Coffee consumption and heart disease</strong>:\n\n\t\t\t\t<ul>\n<li>Initial studies suggested coffee consumption is <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"8d0fca798b1692777191b6cd41880f\">linked</span> to heart disease.</li>\n<li>However, smoking (a confounder) was later found to be more prevalent among coffee drinkers and the real cause of the observed association.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>3. Direct (Causal)</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>An association where the predictor directly influences the outcome.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Smoking and lung cancer</strong>:\n\n\t\t\t\t<ul>\n<li>Smoking directly increases the risk of lung cancer through the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"0b1500fcd816927771900b59d16bde\">inhalation</span> of carcinogens.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0a. One-to-One causal\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0(Option C)</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>A direct causal link between a single predictor and a single outcome.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Vitamin C <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"209b85faf71692777185767d43e3bd\">deficiency</span> and scurvy</strong>:\n\n\t\t\t\t<ul>\n<li>Lack of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"964b8993a1169277720279c9c96cd1\">vitamin C</span> (predictor) directly causes <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"0eff347651169277719862eb775130\">scurvy</span> (outcome).</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0b. Multifactorial</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>An association involving multiple factors contributing to the outcome.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n\n\n<p style='font-size: 10px; color: #808080; font-style: italic;'></p>",
